The paper deals with the problem of neighbor discovery in wireless networks, which involves signal processing, information theory, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves networked systems, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another likely category. The compressed sensing technique used in the paper is a form of data compression, which suggests cs.SI (Signal Processing) as a possible category. The paper also involves solving a sparse recovery problem, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the complexity of the decoding algorithm, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
